What kind of company would Jeff Bezos start if he were 30 years old today?=
=C2=A0
Bezos founded Amazon.com when he was 30 years old, back in 1994. Today, it=
=E2=80=99s the fifth most valuable company in the world, with a $1.75 trill=
ion market cap. Bezos himself is the richest person in the world and the on=
ly one out of the 7.9 billion of us with a net worth over $200 billion. He =
recently flew to space on his own company=E2=80=99s spaceship. He=E2=80=99s=
 done well, and everyone knows it.
The incredible part of the Amazon story to me, though, is how and why it st=
arted.=C2=A0
Other companies have built better business models than Amazon. Google and F=
acebook are money-printing machines, which Ben Thompson calls Super Aggrega=
tors [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE1uhDAMhU8z2Q3KHzQssuim10AmMRAV=
